就是绿票讹诈。
但是这最后还是完成了

301
00:20:20,445 --> 00:20:23,781
- It's terrorism, and I won't do it!
- We have other options, don't we?
-这是恐怖主义，我不会做的！
-我们有其他选择吗？

302
00:20:23,949 --> 00:20:25,700
Well, you're gonna lose your company.
嗯，你将会失去你的公司。

303
00:20:25,867 --> 00:20:27,827
Like hell I am.
我喜欢地狱吗

304
00:20:27,994 --> 00:20:31,622
You, as they say in the street,
are in play.
你正在比赛，像他们在大街上说的

305
00:20:32,082 --> 00:20:34,167
Garfield put you there.
加菲尔德让你在这儿（跟他比赛）

306
00:20:34,626 --> 00:20:37,336
And now I'm here as your lawyer.
现在我在这作为你的律师

307
00:20:37,837 --> 00:20:40,005
Isn't that a hell of an irony?
这是不是一个糟透的讽刺？

308
00:20:40,173 --> 00:20:43,509
Me trying to save your company.
我正试图拯救你的公司

309
00:20:43,635 --> 00:20:46,179
Well, I can do it.
是的，这是我能做的

310
00:20:57,982 --> 00:20:59,233
Yeah?
是

311
00:20:59,358 --> 00:21:01,943
A Miss Sullivan
from Hudson,  Bradley and Flint is here,
在这里有一位从哈得逊，布拉德利来的沙利文小姐

312
00:21:02,153 --> 00:21:04,113
And Granger wants to see you
about Trundel,
还有，格兰杰因为Trundel的事想见你

313
00:21:04,238 --> 00:21:07,032
Your suits are ready for a fitting,
Can they come up at 5?
你的衣服需要试衣，他们可以5点来吗？

314
00:21:07,158 --> 00:21:11,203
Yeah, 5:OO is okay. But tell them not to
send the blind son of a bitch with the pins.
是的，5点可以。但是告诉他们不要派狗娘养的愚昧的别针来

315
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:14,039
- Right, no pins,
- And tell Granger, if he wants to see me...
-好的，不要针脚
-告诉格兰杰，如果他想见我……

316
00:21:14,206 --> 00:21:17,709
...he better make more sense than last time,
or he can get on unemployment.
……他最好比上次做得更有意义，或者他将失业。

317
00:21:17,835 --> 00:21:19,670
Shall I use those exact words, sir?
我要用这些话，先生？

318
00:21:19,795 --> 00:21:22,214
Send in Hudson, Bradley and Flint.
让哈得逊，布拉德利的人进来

319
00:21:40,315 --> 00:21:41,983
Wow.
噢

320
00:21:43,985 --> 00:21:47,571
You know what kills me? I've done
maybe seven, eight deals like this before...
你知道我讨厌什么吗? 
这样的事之前我大概遇上了七、八件……

321
00:21:47,781 --> 00:21:49,491
...and you know who I negotiate with?
……你知道谁与我洽谈？

322
00:21:49,657 --> 00:21:53,410
Skinny little joggers with contact lenses,
all stinking from the same aftershave.
苗条的着贴身小套装，同样的后须水的味道

323
00:21:53,620 --> 00:21:54,912
- I'm Kate Sullivan.
- I know.
-我是凯特沙利文
-我知道

324
00:21:55,079 --> 00:21:57,039
- Want a cigarette?
- No, thank you.
-要一支烟吗？
-不，谢谢

325
00:21:58,082 --> 00:21:59,625
Don't let me stop you.
别让我阻止你。

326
00:22:01,294 --> 00:22:03,421
Why would you stop me?
为什么要阻止我？

327
00:22:03,588 --> 00:22:05,506
What are you, a fucking lawyer?
你是什么，一个他妈的律师？

328
00:22:05,673 --> 00:22:07,257
Depends on who I'm with.
取决于我和谁在一起

329
00:22:08,342 --> 00:22:10,302
Welcome to my life.
欢迎来到我的生活

330
00:22:10,470 --> 00:22:12,096
So, what's it gonna be?
因此，接下来是什么？

331
00:22:12,263 --> 00:22:14,890
Sue, settle, defend?
起诉，协议，辩护?

332
00:22:15,057 --> 00:22:16,558
I came to talk.
我是来对话的。

333
00:22:17,852 --> 00:22:19,562
Oh, that's trouble.
哦，那就麻烦了

334
00:22:19,770 --> 00:22:22,898
Lawyers wanna talk,
nothing but trouble.
律师想谈，只有麻烦

335
00:22:23,065 --> 00:22:25,609
- How about a doughnut?
- No, thanks.
-来一个甜甜圈？
-不了，谢谢。

336
00:22:26,610 --> 00:22:29,738
- Why, are you a health-food freak?
- No, just not hungry.
-为什么，你是保健食品狂吗？
-不，只是不饿。

337
00:22:29,905 --> 00:22:32,407
- You have to be hungry to eat a doughnut?
- You don't?
-你必须饿了才吃一个甜甜圈吗?
-你不吗？

338
00:22:32,783 --> 00:22:33,992
What, are you shitting me?
什么，你在取笑我吗?

339
00:22:34,159 --> 00:22:36,703
I never heard of such a thing,
have to be hungry.
我从未听说过这样的事情，必须是饥饿才吃

340
00:22:36,870 --> 00:22:38,871
Why? It don't taste better that way.
为什么？这样不更美味吗

341
00:22:39,039 --> 00:22:41,416
- How would you know?
- What do you want?
-你怎么知道？
-你想怎么样？

342
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:44,294
- I need a month.
- Get lost.
-我需要一个月
-不行

343
00:22:44,461 --> 00:22:48,214
I just got involved. I need time to get
everybody's act together.
我只是参与了，我需要时间去让大家一起行动。

344
00:22:48,382 --> 00:22:49,674
My act is together.
我的行为是在一起的。

345
00:22:51,259 --> 00:22:54,845
If you give me some time,
I think we can work something out.
如果你给我一点时间，我觉得我们可以做点什么。

346
00:22:55,889 --> 00:22:57,390
Settle?
协议？

347
00:22:57,557 --> 00:22:58,808
Work something out.
工作出一些东西

348
00:22:59,392 --> 00:23:02,603
- I only settle when I'm in trouble.
- Or when it makes sense.
-当我处在麻烦中的时候我才协议。
-或者这样做有意义。

349
00:23:03,396 --> 00:23:05,231
It only makes sense when I'm in trouble.
只我我在麻烦中的时候它才有意义

350
00:23:06,399 --> 00:23:08,359
Well, if you prefer, we'll go to court.
好吧，如果你喜欢，我们可以法庭上见

351
00:23:08,526 --> 00:23:12,446
Get an injunction, have a fight.
All kinds of allegations.
申请一个禁令，来一场战斗。
各种指控。

352
00:23:12,614 --> 00:23:14,782
Costs them, costs you, and for what?
让他们花费，让你花费，这样做又有什么好处？

353
00:23:15,366 --> 00:23:17,534
I live in court.
You gotta do better than that.
我住在法院。
你要做的比这更好。

354
00:23:23,291 --> 00:23:25,751
I won't love you anymore.
我不会再爱你

355
00:23:28,212 --> 00:23:30,672
- Two weeks.
- Standstill agreement.
-两周
-暂停偿付协议

356
00:23:31,507 --> 00:23:33,342
- Both sides.
- No more buying.
-双方
-别买更多

357
00:23:33,509 --> 00:23:35,844
- Two weeks.
- Thank you.
-两周
-谢谢

358
00:23:36,053 --> 00:23:37,262
Whoa, where are you going?
哇，你要去哪里？

359
00:23:37,430 --> 00:23:40,140
We haven't talked about
what I wanna talk about.
我们还没聊我想说的。

360
00:23:40,307 --> 00:23:45,103
- What's that?
- You and me sweating between satin sheets.
-聊什么
-我和你在缎子床单上出汗。

361
00:23:46,689 --> 00:23:50,734
Garfield, put your hand between your legs.
加菲尔德，把你的手放在你的腿中间。

362
00:23:51,610 --> 00:23:52,944
Do it!
做啊

363
00:23:54,530 --> 00:23:57,950
Good. Now look directly down
at that little guy...
很好，现在，直拉看下这小家伙……

364
00:23:58,117 --> 00:24:02,621
...and you say, "You must behave yourself
when you're in the presence of a lady."
……你说，“你必须表现的像绅士当你在女士面前。”

365
00:24:02,788 --> 00:24:07,000
Garfield, if you don't say exactly that
right now, I'm resigning from this case.
加菲尔德，如果你不照我说的做，我会辞退这个案例。

366
00:24:11,129 --> 00:24:14,340
- You must behave yourself...
- You must behave yourself...
-你必须表现的像绅士……
-你必须表现的像绅士……

367
00:24:14,508 --> 00:24:17,677
...when you're in the presence...
...when you're in the presence...
……当你在一个女士面前……
……当你在一个女士面前……

368
00:24:17,886 --> 00:24:19,846
...of a lady.

369
00:24:23,975 --> 00:24:27,103
See? Not so hard.
看到了吗？不是很难。

370
00:24:38,198 --> 00:24:40,283
See you in two weeks.
两周后见。

371
00:24:41,326 --> 00:24:43,369
Wow! Did you see that, Carmen?
哇！你看到了吗，卡门？

372
00:24:44,746 --> 00:24:46,372
I'm in love, I'm in love.
我恋爱了，我恋爱了。

373
00:24:46,539 --> 00:24:48,749
- Goodbye, Miss Sullivan.
- Goodbye.
-再见，沙利文小姐。
-再见。

374
00:25:04,723 --> 00:25:08,017
Call Erickson. Tell him to arrange
some money through the Royal Bank.
打电话给埃里克森。告诉他通过皇家银行安排一些钱。

375
00:25:08,227 --> 00:25:10,437
Don't pay more than we did
on Fleetwood Furniture.
费用不要超过我们做佛利特伍德家俱时的

376
00:25:10,604 --> 00:25:11,980
Then call Hathaway.
然后打电话给哈撒伟

377
00:25:12,147 --> 00:25:15,316
Tell him I want to make a tender offer
for New England Wire and Cable.
告诉他，我想为新英格兰电线电缆公司做一下投标报价

378
00:25:15,484 --> 00:25:16,818
Don't put it under our name.
不要把我们的名字写进去

379
00:25:16,985 --> 00:25:19,153
Label it OPM Holdings.
标签OPM控股

380
00:25:19,321 --> 00:25:21,656
But what if she finds out
we broke the agreement?
但如果她发现我们打破协议呢？

381
00:25:23,575 --> 00:25:25,702
Richardson, what were you,
born yesterday?
理查德森，你怎么了，你是出生在昨天吗？

382
00:25:25,827 --> 00:25:27,662
What do you think she's doing?
你觉得她在做什么？

383
00:25:27,788 --> 00:25:30,707
That kewpie doll's up to no good.
Do it.
丘比娃娃不怀好意。
做就是了。

384
00:25:31,208 --> 00:25:34,753
I got us an extra two weeks.
Now we have to move fast.
我为我们多争取了两周时间。
现在我们们必须快速行动。

385
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:37,547
Get the board to buy up as many shares
as they can.
让董事会尽所能的买入更多的股份。

386
00:25:37,672 --> 00:25:39,507
Use your own working capital.
用你的营运资金

387
00:25:39,633 --> 00:25:41,551
No,  that's not what
those dollars are for,
不，那些钱不是做这个用的，

388
00:25:41,718 --> 00:25:44,387
- That's our safety net,
- Then borrow the money.
-那是我们的安全网
-再借点钱

389
00:25:44,512 --> 00:25:48,140
- No borrowing.
- Andrew, listen to her. She's making sense.
-不借钱。
-安得烈，听她的，她这样做有意义

390
00:25:48,266 --> 00:25:52,186
For every share you acquire,
it's one less for Garfield,
你每多获得一份股份，加菲尔德就少一份股份。

391
00:25:52,312 --> 00:25:54,856
The more we buy, the less for him.
我们买的越多，他就越少。

392
00:25:55,064 --> 00:25:57,900
The more it costs, the less profit he makes.
成本越高，他的利润就越少。

393
00:25:58,067 --> 00:25:59,485
So get the stock up.
这样股价就上去了。

394
00:25:59,652 --> 00:26:02,446
And, Mom, make sure to buy it
through an out-of-state broker.
然后，妈妈，确保要通过一个外州的经纪人买入

395
00:26:02,613 --> 00:26:06,992
I don't wanna borrow money.
We've been debt-free since the depression.
我不想借钱
自从萧条期，我们就没有债务了。

396
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:09,120
But see, that's the trouble, Jorgy.
但看吧，那就是问题，jorgy.

397
00:26:09,287 --> 00:26:12,873
It's your gorgeous balance sheet
that makes you so attractive.
就是你这华丽的资产负债表让你变得这么有吸引力。

398
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:15,375
And, Mom, get letters out
to the shareholders.
妈妈，把信发给股东。

399
00:26:15,543 --> 00:26:19,171
Tell them how great business is
and how wonderful the future looks,
告诉他们这是多好的生意，看上去前景多少好。


400
00:26:19,338 --> 00:26:20,964
- I'll do it.
- Great,
-我会做的
-太好了

401
00:26:21,132 --> 00:26:24,635
I'll call you tomorrow.
Good night.
我明天再联系你，晚安。

402
00:26:48,450 --> 00:26:51,202
Good morning, honey.
早上好，亲爱的

403
00:26:58,460 --> 00:27:01,504
How you doing this morning, huh?
你今天早上怎么样了，嗯？

404
00:27:09,304 --> 00:27:11,180
You got it up again.
你又上涨了。

405
00:27:12,182 --> 00:27:14,058
Another point and a half.
又一个1.5点

406
00:27:14,726 --> 00:27:16,477
- Pfeiffer.
- Good morning, Mr. Garfield.
-菲佛。
-早上好，加菲尔德先生

407
00:27:16,644 --> 00:27:18,354
- Woody.
- Good morning, Mr. Garfield.
-伍迪
-早上好，加菲尔德先生

408
00:27:18,563 --> 00:27:19,772
- Harriet.
- Good morning.
-哈丽特
-早上好

409
00:27:19,981 --> 00:27:22,024
Miss Sullivan is gonna call
tomorrow morning.
沙利文小姐明早会打电话来。

410
00:27:22,191 --> 00:27:24,318
You tell her I'm not taking calls.
你告诉她我不接电话

411
00:27:24,485 --> 00:27:27,613
Then, when she comes over here
and tries to storm into the office...
如果，她来这里，并试图闯入办公室……

412
00:27:27,822 --> 00:27:30,324
...you try to keep her out.
But then let her push past.
……你要试图阻止她，但最后让她通过。

413
00:27:30,491 --> 00:27:35,495
Don't worry, she's desperate but harmless.
Find out where she lives and call a florist.
别担心，她会有点绝望但无害。
找出她住在哪里，打电话给花店。

414
00:27:36,163 --> 00:27:37,497
- Florist?
- Florist.
-花店?
-花店。

415
00:27:42,002 --> 00:27:44,921
You have a good evening, Miss Sullivan.
祝你有一个美好的夜晚，沙利文小姐。

416
00:27:46,882 --> 00:27:50,385
- Hello, Michael.
- Oh, Miss Sullivan, here.
-你好，迈克尔。
-哦，沙利文，在这里。

417
00:27:50,552 --> 00:27:53,554
- Somebody brought these by for you.
- Oh, thank you.
-有人把这些给你。
-哦，谢谢

418
00:27:53,722 --> 00:27:55,682
- Good night.
- Good night.
-晚安。
-晚安。

419
00:28:46,899 --> 00:28:48,692
- Good morning.
- Good morning.
-早上好。
-早上好。

420
00:28:53,489 --> 00:28:57,451
- You ruthless son of a bitch!
- Excuse me?
-你这混蛋！
-怎么了？

421
00:28:57,618 --> 00:28:59,369
Jeez, I wonder what her problem is.
耶稣啊，我不知道她有什么问题。

422
00:29:18,889 --> 00:29:20,890
All right, all right.
好的，好的。

423
00:29:26,813 --> 00:29:28,022
Excuse me.
抱歉。

424
00:29:28,190 --> 00:29:31,860
- Hello, Miss Sullivan, may I help you?
- No, I'm sorry. I don't care. I will...
-你好,沙利文小姐，我可以帮你吗？
-不，抱歉。我不在乎，我……

425
00:29:32,903 --> 00:29:36,323
- I don't care! I'm not gonna...
- It's all right, Harriet.
-我不在乎！我不是想要……
-没关系的，哈丽特。

426
00:29:36,490 --> 00:29:39,534
- You can't go in.
- It's not all right, you hypocrite! You lied!
-你不能进去。
-这并不好，你这假冒的伪善人，你说谎了！

427
00:29:40,368 --> 00:29:42,620
- But, baby-poo...
- We had an agreement.
-但是，宝贝……
-我们有过协议的。

428
00:29:42,746 --> 00:29:45,540
We had a standstill!
No more buying!
我们都要停下来，不是更多的买入！

429
00:29:45,665 --> 00:29:49,085
- OPM Holdings? You know nothing about it?
- OPM?
-OPM 控股？你对此一无所知？
-OPM？

430
00:29:49,252 --> 00:29:51,962
- Not a lot to know.
- You broke the agreement!
-一点也不知道。
-你破坏了协议！

431
00:29:52,130 --> 00:29:55,466
You embarrassed me with my firm.
You embarrassed me with my clients!
你让我对我公司很窘。
你让我对我的客户很窘！

432
00:29:55,633 --> 00:29:57,301
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
等等，等等。

433
00:29:57,427 --> 00:29:59,720
Don't come on so holier-than-thou with me.
别对我假仁假义的

434
00:29:59,929 --> 00:30:03,182
What am I supposed to do,
sit here while you drive up the stock?
我能怎么办，坐在这里干等你抬高股价？

435
00:30:03,349 --> 00:30:06,143
- I did no such thing.
- You're full of shit.
-我没有做这种事。
-你在胡扯

436
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:10,188
All that buying coming from some little
cockamamie brokerage firm in Rhode Island?
所有买入都来自罗得岛的众多的经纪公司？

437
00:30:10,356 --> 00:30:12,399
You'd think you'd use an out-of-state firm.
你肯定想过要用一个外州的注册

438
00:30:12,608 --> 00:30:14,234
I know nothing about that.
我对此事一无所知

439
00:30:14,443 --> 00:30:15,694
Give me a break.
你就省省吧

440
00:30:15,861 --> 00:30:18,113
Who am I dealing with here,
Mother Teresa?
我是在与谁打交道，特瑞萨修女？

441
00:30:18,280 --> 00:30:20,657
You want to play the game,
learn to play it right.
你想玩这游戏，学会如何玩好它。

442
00:30:20,783 --> 00:30:23,493
Oh, is that what you call it,
a game?
哦，这就是你所说的，一场游戏？

443
00:30:23,661 --> 00:30:26,330
You're damn right.
The best game in the world.
你说对了，这世上最棒的游戏。

444
00:30:26,497 --> 00:30:28,498
I'll teach you. It's easy.
我来教你，很容易。

445
00:30:28,624 --> 00:30:31,334
You make as much as you can
for as long as you can.
你要尽你所能的尽可能的多做

446
00:30:31,502 --> 00:30:32,711
And then what?
然后呢？

447
00:30:33,212 --> 00:30:34,504
"And then what?"
然后？

448
00:30:34,672 --> 00:30:36,965
Whoever has the most when he dies,
wins.
当他死亡或胜利的时候，那个人将拥有更多

