00:42:09,769 --> 00:42:12,646
- Except for the stockholders.
- Their stock falls out of bed...
-除了股东
-他们的股价跌到地板上了……

615
00:42:12,772 --> 00:42:16,275
...they don't know what hit them.
- Now you're Albert Schweitzer.
……他们不知道是什么袭击了他们
-现在你成了史怀哲了

616
00:42:16,442 --> 00:42:19,695
No, not Albert Schweitzer,
Robin Hood.
不，不是史怀哲，是罗宾汉。

617
00:42:19,862 --> 00:42:22,781
I take from the rich,
and I give to the middle class.
我把从富人那里拿来的钱分给中产阶级。

618
00:42:22,948 --> 00:42:24,366
Well, the upper middle class.
嗯，上层中产阶级。

619
00:42:24,533 --> 00:42:26,952
- Would you care for some caviar?
- The stock is 18.
-你要些鱼子酱吗？
-现在的股价是18.

620
00:42:27,119 --> 00:42:28,495
Do you like music? The violin?
你喜欢音乐吗？小提琴的怎么？

621
00:42:28,662 --> 00:42:31,664
- Let's be serious.
- Come on, let's change the subject.
-我们是认真的。
-好吧，我们换个话题吧。

622
00:42:31,832 --> 00:42:36,211
- Arthur.
- The stock is 18. We'll buy it back at 18.
-亚瑟
-现在股价是18美元每股，我们用18美元每股买回来

623
00:42:36,378 --> 00:42:39,255
- First you laugh at me, then you insult me.
- Then name your number.
-开始时你取笑我，现在你又侮辱我
-那告诉我你的数字

624
00:42:39,464 --> 00:42:41,340
- What will you take?
- Twenty-five.
-你想要多少？
-25美元每股

625
00:42:41,508 --> 00:42:43,509
The stock hasn't seen 25 in years.
股价已经没到25几年了。

626
00:42:43,677 --> 00:42:45,887
You want history?
The stock was once 8O.
你想知道历史股价？股价曾经到达过80美元

627
00:42:46,096 --> 00:42:47,514
Take 2O.
20怎么样

628
00:42:47,723 --> 00:42:49,015
Such a high achiever.
很诱人的价格

629
00:42:49,182 --> 00:42:51,559
If you're mad at somebody,
don't take it out on me.
如果你迷上了某人，不要发泄在我身上。

630
00:42:51,685 --> 00:42:53,728
Twenty-five is my number,
and that's a favor.
我出价是25，那是偏爱。

631
00:42:53,895 --> 00:42:57,106
Well, I don't like your number,
and I don't need to be analyzed.
嗯，我不喜欢你的报价，我也不需要分析

632
00:42:57,274 --> 00:42:58,650
Do we have a deal or not?
我们能达成协议吗？

633
00:42:58,817 --> 00:43:00,193
Let's discuss it over dinner.
让我们在晚餐时讨论吧

634
00:43:00,360 --> 00:43:03,905
- Good night. Your 2O minutes are up.
- Wait a minute. I want us to be friends.
-晚安，你的20分钟已经过了
-请稍等，我希望我们能成为朋友。

635
00:43:04,072 --> 00:43:07,200
Let's segue into some soup
and french bread.
让我们继续些汤和法国面包吧


636
00:43:08,243 --> 00:43:10,578
Come on. Don't go away mad.
来吧，不要生气离开

637
00:43:10,745 --> 00:43:13,414
I didn't buy your proposition.
Come back with another one.
我没有买你的主张，回给给我另一个。

638
00:43:13,581 --> 00:43:16,875
You're an emancipated woman.
Learn to lose.
你是一个自由的女人，学会失败

639
00:43:17,043 --> 00:43:19,420
- I haven't lost.
- Wait, wait!
-我没有失败。
-等等

640
00:43:19,587 --> 00:43:22,965
I got a proposition for you.
Hold on, you gotta listen.
我有个建议给你，坚持下去，你一定要听

641
00:43:23,758 --> 00:43:25,134
You come on back up.
你回来

642
00:43:25,301 --> 00:43:27,219
We have a nice dinner.
我们来一个不错的晚餐

643
00:43:28,304 --> 00:43:31,390
We make passionate love
for the rest of the night.
在剩下的夜里，我们可以激情的做爱

644
00:43:32,099 --> 00:43:34,809
The first one who comes, loses.
这第一个来的，是失败一方

645
00:43:36,020 --> 00:43:38,021
- Loses what?
- The deal.
-关于什么失败
-这个协议

646
00:43:38,230 --> 00:43:41,858
I come first, I sell you back
my shares at cost.
我第一个来，我以成本价把我的股份卖还给你

647
00:43:42,026 --> 00:43:45,362
You come first, you buy them at 25.
你第一个来，你出价25美元买回它们

648
00:43:47,489 --> 00:43:49,490
I think you're serious.
我想你是认真的

649
00:43:50,492 --> 00:43:53,119
So how do you suggest
we write this up?
你怎么认为，要我写上吗？

650
00:43:54,163 --> 00:43:55,497
Delicately.
不错

651
00:43:55,664 --> 00:43:59,459
Under the heading,
"Easy come, easy go."
标题写上，“来的容易，去的容易。”

652
00:43:59,626 --> 00:44:03,796
What do you got to lose, your virginity?
I could lose millions.
你会失去什么，你的贞操？
我可以失去数百万。

653
00:44:05,340 --> 00:44:08,384
So, what happens if we come together?
所以，如果我们在一起会发生什么?

654
00:44:11,805 --> 00:44:13,598
I never thought of that.
我从没想过那个

655
00:44:15,892 --> 00:44:17,643
Well...
怎么样……

656
00:44:17,769 --> 00:44:19,854
...think about it, honey.
……考虑一下，亲爱的。

657
00:44:20,063 --> 00:44:22,565
I will. I will.
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
我会的，我会的
等等，等等

658
00:44:22,732 --> 00:44:24,900
Come on. Don't go.
来吧，不要走

659
00:44:25,068 --> 00:44:27,862
I haven't played my violin yet.
到现在我还没有拉我的小提琴呢。

660
00:46:30,649 --> 00:46:33,234
Oh, God.
哦，神啊

661
00:46:35,696 --> 00:46:37,697
Hello?
你好?

662
00:46:38,782 --> 00:46:40,825
I just wanted to see if you got home safe.
我只想知道你已经安全到家

663
00:46:42,160 --> 00:46:44,287
Thank you.
谢谢

664
00:46:45,372 --> 00:46:47,832
In your beddy-bye?
你在床上？

665
00:46:48,667 --> 00:46:50,585
I am.
我是

666
00:46:51,628 --> 00:46:53,588
- Did I wake you?
- No.
-我吵醒你了吗
-没

667
00:46:53,755 --> 00:46:55,173
No.
没

668
00:46:56,883 --> 00:47:00,177
- Did you have dinner?
- Yes.
-你吃过晚餐了吗
-是的

669
00:47:00,345 --> 00:47:02,388
With who?
和谁

670
00:47:02,555 --> 00:47:04,932
None of your business.
不关你的事

671
00:47:08,311 --> 00:47:10,479
- Are you thinking about me?
- No.
-你想我了吗？
-没

672
00:47:10,605 --> 00:47:14,025
Well, how could
you possibly manage that?
嗯，怎么可能你可能办到的？

673
00:47:14,192 --> 00:47:17,570
Pills, whiskey, self-help tapes.
丸，威士忌，自助录音带。

674
00:47:22,116 --> 00:47:24,201
I got another proposition for you.
我有另一个建议给你

675
00:47:24,368 --> 00:47:26,578
Oh,  yeah? I can't wait,
听，是吗？我等不及了

676
00:47:26,746 --> 00:47:28,372
We swap.
我们交换

677
00:47:30,124 --> 00:47:33,001
Swap what, dirty jokes?
交换什么，肮脏的笑话吗？

678
00:47:35,045 --> 00:47:36,755
No. I give you all my shares...
不，我给你我所有的股份……

679
00:47:36,881 --> 00:47:39,300
...you give me the wire and cable division.
……你给我电线电缆公司。

680
00:47:41,719 --> 00:47:43,262
Hello?
在吗？

681
00:47:43,679 --> 00:47:45,597
Hello? You like?
在吗，你喜欢吗？

682
00:47:45,723 --> 00:47:48,892
- I'll ask them.
- Good.
-我问一下他们。
-好的

683
00:47:49,059 --> 00:47:52,479
All right, now wait. Don't go away.
Don't hang up. Don't hang up.
好的，先等会，别走开。
别挂线，别挂线。

684
00:47:52,604 --> 00:47:55,148
Stay right where you are. All right.
就呆在你现在呆的地方，好吗

685
00:47:57,025 --> 00:47:58,526
Okay.
好的

686
00:48:38,983 --> 00:48:40,859
Here comes the bridge.
这里是桥

687
00:49:27,948 --> 00:49:29,532
That was very good.
这里非常好

688
00:49:29,741 --> 00:49:31,742
- Thank you.
- You're welcome,
-谢谢
-你是受欢迎的

689
00:49:31,952 --> 00:49:33,328
That was just for you.
那是只为你做的

690
00:49:33,536 --> 00:49:35,204
Well, I appreciate it.
嗯，我很感激

691
00:49:35,372 --> 00:49:36,873
Sweet dreams,
甜蜜的梦

692
00:49:36,998 --> 00:49:40,543
- Okay. Good night.
- Bye-bye.
-好的， 晚安
-再见

693
00:49:42,087 --> 00:49:44,297
Oh, God.
哦，天啊

694
00:50:11,866 --> 00:50:13,325
Forget it.
忘了这吧

695
00:50:13,492 --> 00:50:15,744
Tell him to go to hell.
告诉他去地狱吧

696
00:50:15,911 --> 00:50:18,997
He spends $ 1 3 million for this place...
他在这儿花了13百万……

697
00:50:19,206 --> 00:50:21,291
...then he sells it for 35.
……现在他要卖35百万。

698
00:50:21,458 --> 00:50:25,211
My guys are out of work,
and he's made $ 22 million.
我的人失去了工作
他确赚了22百万

699
00:50:25,379 --> 00:50:28,632
- Now how do I live with that?
- We eliminate a losing division.
-现我我怎么活呢？
-我们消除了一个失败的公司

700
00:50:28,757 --> 00:50:31,176
The other divisions don't have
to support us anymore.
其它公司再也不用支持我们了

701
00:50:31,343 --> 00:50:33,762
- I don't wanna hear that.
- You still control the company.
-我不想听到这些
-你仍然控制公司

702
00:50:33,929 --> 00:50:37,057
- You just don't have the cable division.
- Why is it so difficult...
-你只是没有电线电缆公司
-为什么这样难……

703
00:50:37,224 --> 00:50:38,725
...for everybody to understand...
……让每个人都明白……

704
00:50:38,934 --> 00:50:41,978
...why I can't kill these people
and this town...
……为什么我不能杀了这个镇上的那些人……

705
00:50:42,187 --> 00:50:45,773
...to enrich some son of a bitch
who's trying to destroy me?
……狗娘养的试图靠毁掉我来发财？

706
00:50:45,982 --> 00:50:48,401
I can't play with him
in the courts forever.
我不指望跟他在法庭上玩

707
00:50:48,568 --> 00:50:51,612
He'll get the injunction lifted
and buy more shares.
他会让禁令解除并买更多的股票

708
00:50:51,780 --> 00:50:54,657
Don't be a pigheaded fool.
不要做一个固执的笨蛋了。

709
00:50:54,824 --> 00:50:57,201
He deserves to lose this company.
他理应失去这个公司

710
00:51:08,504 --> 00:51:11,465
- Good night, Mr. Jorgenson.
- Good night, Gus.
-晚安，乔根森先生
-晚安，格斯

711
00:51:11,633 --> 00:51:13,718
Everything going along okay,
Mr. Jorgenson?
一切顺利吗，乔根森先生

712
00:51:13,926 --> 00:51:15,636
Everything's moving right along, Gus.
一切进展顺利，格斯

713
00:51:15,803 --> 00:51:18,513
Everything's gonna be okay,
isn't it, at the plant?
一切还好吗，在这工厂里？

714
00:51:18,639 --> 00:51:21,933
- I mean, at the plant and everything?
- Everything's gonna be just fine.
-我的意思是，在这工厂的里每一件事？
-每件事都不错

715
00:51:22,101 --> 00:51:24,811
We'll be making wire and cable
for a long time.
我们会继续做电线电缆很长一段时间

716
00:51:24,979 --> 00:51:27,981
- Yes, sir. Good night, sir.
- Good night.
-是的，先生，晚安，先生
-晚安

717
00:51:31,193 --> 00:51:32,861
Jorgy?
jorgy?

718
00:51:34,029 --> 00:51:36,781
- Have you got a minute?
- Sure, Bill.
-你有时间吗？
-当然，比尔

719
00:51:38,617 --> 00:51:41,536
Do you mind if I speak frankly
to you, Jorgy?
你介意我跟你坦白说话吗，jorgy?

720
00:51:42,579 --> 00:51:44,455
You always have, haven't you?
你总是，不是吗？

721
00:51:45,749 --> 00:51:47,000
You know...
你知道……

722
00:51:47,167 --> 00:51:50,420
...I'm trained to think in contingency.
……我参加入应急培训。

723
00:51:50,587 --> 00:51:53,172
You know I've spent my life
managing businesses, and...
你知道我花了毕生管理生意，和……

724
00:51:53,799 --> 00:51:55,258
And...
和……

725
00:51:55,425 --> 00:51:58,010
Bill, you're in a panic.
比尔，你有点惊慌。

726
00:51:58,679 --> 00:52:01,056
Well, you know how it is
with business, Jorgy.
嗯，你知道生意的事的，Jorgy

727
00:52:01,223 --> 00:52:03,850
When things don't work out quite right...
当事情不好解决时……

728
00:52:04,059 --> 00:52:08,479
...and people have invested a lot of time,
a lot of their energy, a lot of themselves...
……又当人们在其中投入了很多的时间，投入了很多他们的精力，很多他们自已的……

729
00:52:08,647 --> 00:52:11,775
...management takes care of its own, Jorgy.
It happens all the time.
……管理照顾自已，jorgy.
这是常有的事。

730
00:52:11,942 --> 00:52:16,946
And given the uncertainty
surrounding us these days...
这阵子我我们周边的环境并不确定……

731
00:52:18,114 --> 00:52:22,618
...and the fact that you haven't set up
any financial guarantees for us, Jorgy...
……事实上，你还没有为我们设立任何财务担保，jorgy……

732
00:52:25,205 --> 00:52:28,916
Lord, I hate...
Hate giving this speech.
上帝，我痛恨……
痛恨这样说

733
00:52:29,083 --> 00:52:33,545
When I retire in two years, I've told you,
you're taking over the business.
我告诉过你的，当两年后我将退休，到时你将接手生意。

734
00:52:33,713 --> 00:52:35,131
I promised you that.
我答应过你的

735
00:52:35,298 --> 00:52:38,634
There won't be any business
in two years, Jorgy.
两年后不会有任何生意了，jorgy.

736
00:52:38,843 --> 00:52:41,470
There won't be any business in one year.
一年后也不见得会有生意。

737
00:52:42,430 --> 00:52:44,390
You're holding on to a dream.
那是你的幻想

738
00:52:45,308 --> 00:52:47,476
Go home, Bill. Have a drink.
回家吧，比尔，去喝一杯。

739
00:52:47,685 --> 00:52:50,229
Give my best to Jeanette.
帮我向珍妮问好

740
00:52:50,730 --> 00:52:54,358
I don't want the rug pulled out
from under me so close to the finish line.
我并不想撤出，当离终点线如此的时候

741
00:52:55,568 --> 00:52:57,569
Good night.
晚安

742
00:52:58,362 --> 00:53:01,615
Jorgy, I've been here 1 5 years.
I have a family. Something's due me.
我已经在这里15年了，我有一个家，我还期望有所得呢

743
00:53:01,782 --> 00:53:04,034
Now, I've worked my ass off
for 1 5 years...
现在，你在这个位置坐了15年……

744
00:53:04,201 --> 00:53:08,204
...and you're gonna let that man come in
and take over the company. It's not right.
……你确要让那个人参于进来并接管公司，这不对。

745
00:53:10,207 --> 00:53:11,833
I'm sorry, Bill.
抱歉，比尔。

746
00:53:12,042 --> 00:53:16,129
Up here we don't plan the funeral
until the body is dead.
我不打算在这举行葬礼，直到我死了。

747
00:53:27,516 --> 00:53:29,726
Sounds like everybody's hungry.
看上去每个都很饿。

748
00:53:29,893 --> 00:53:31,978
Well, let's eat.
好吧，让我的开动吧

749
00:53:32,187 --> 00:53:34,439
- Sit down, darling.
- Happy Thanksgiving.
-请坐，亲受的。
-感恩节快乐

750
00:53:38,818 --> 00:53:41,612
Thank thee, Father, for thy care,
for thy bounty everywhere.
感谢你，主，感谢你的关怀，你的慷慨无处不在

751
00:53:41,780 --> 00:53:45,575
For this and every other gift,
our grateful hearts to thee we lift.
真诚的感激主所赋我们这以及所有其它礼物

752
00:53:45,742 --> 00:53:47,243
Amen.
啊门

753
00:53:57,420 --> 00:53:59,421
Second down and 1 O, Lions at their 49,
在10码处第二次进攻，狮子队在49的位置，

754
00:53:59,589 --> 00:54:02,466
I don't know why you watch this.
It's so stupid!
我不知道为什么你会看这么，看上去很愚蠢！

755
00:54:02,592 --> 00:54:05,344
Maybe if you'd watch, you'd see.
See, he's going right now.
如何你在看的话，你会看到，看，他正往前冲

756
00:54:05,511 --> 00:54:07,846
Yes. Go, go, go!
好，冲，冲，冲！

757
00:54:08,014 --> 00:54:11,475
I told you.
My money was on Detroit.
告诉你，我在底特律队上压了钱

758
00:54:30,160 --> 00:54:33,329
Have to admit,
we still have fresh air up here.
必须承认，我们在这里仍然有新鲜空气。

759
00:54:34,122 --> 00:54:35,957
Feels good, all right.
感觉很好

760
00:54:38,585 --> 00:54:41,671
I'm awfully glad you came, Kate.
我很高兴你来了，凯特

761
00:54:41,838 --> 00:54:44,507
It means a hell of a lot to your mother.
对你母亲来说，这意味着很多

762
00:54:45,467 --> 00:54:46,968
I love your mother.
你爱你母亲

763
00:54:47,427 --> 00:54:51,430
I can't say I'm sorry for that,
but I am sorry for whatever it is...
我不能不说我我很抱歉，我很抱歉不管他是什么……

764
00:54:51,640 --> 00:54:55,894
...that it's done to you
in the last 21 - Odd years.
……在过去的21年对你所做的

765
00:54:56,061 --> 00:54:58,480
I'm okay, Jorgy.
我很好，jorgy.

766
00:54:58,688 --> 00:55:00,189
Good.
好的

767
00:55:00,315 --> 00:55:02,734
Now let's talk a little business.
现在我们谈点生意上的事。

768
00:55:02,901 --> 00:55:05,862
Let's quit talking about what I won't do.
我们不要讨论我不会做什么。

769
00:55:06,446 --> 00:55:08,906
Let's talk about what I will do.
让我们讨论一下我将要做什么。

770
00:55:10,241 --> 00:55:11,867
I have a problem.
我遇到麻烦了

771
00:55:12,952 --> 00:55:15,037
I'm a good lawyer.
I'm a lousy mind reader.
我是个好律师。
我是一个只会出瘦主意的人。

772
00:55:15,204 --> 00:55:19,207
I wanna put it to a vote.
Annual meeting in four weeks.
我想在四周后的年度会议上进行投票决议

773
00:55:19,375 --> 00:55:21,794
Wanna put it in the hands
of the stockholders.
想让公司的股东进行表决

774
00:55:21,961 --> 00:55:24,546
Can't do that. It's too risky.
We could lose everything.
不能那样做，太危险了，我会会失去一切的。

775
00:55:24,672 --> 00:55:28,008
- You're a fighter. I'm a fighter.
- It's too dangerous.
-你是一个战士，我是一个战士。
-太危险了

776
00:55:28,634 --> 00:55:32,054
There's no other choice
that I can live with.
我没有其他选择

777
00:55:33,889 --> 00:55:36,975
This 3O percent,
this faithful 3O percent...
30%股份，忠实的30%股份……

778
00:55:37,142 --> 00:55:38,852
...can you absolutely count on them?
……你可以绝对的相信他们？

779
00:55:39,019 --> 00:55:41,229
They haven't let me down so far.
到目前为止他们还没有让我失望过。

780
00:55:41,397 --> 00:55:43,982
Awful lot of Ozzies on our side.
很多像奥齐那样的人支持我们

781
00:55:44,983 --> 00:55:46,901
Don't trust Ozzie. He's a banker.
不要相信奥齐，他是个银行家。

782
00:55:47,361 --> 00:55:50,071
I have to trust my friends, Kate.
我不得不信任我的朋友，凯特。

783
00:55:56,203 --> 00:55:58,455
This is gonna be tough.
这将是棘手的。

784
00:55:58,664 --> 00:56:00,665
I have to get Garfield to buy this.
我已经让加菲尔德买这个了。

785
00:56:01,917 --> 00:56:05,462
He won't want to.
It's not to his advantage.
他不想要的，这不是他的优势。

786
00:56:07,797 --> 00:56:09,590
Talk nice.
很好的谈话

787
00:56:10,550 --> 00:56:12,802
Give him your best smile.
给他最好的笑容

788
00:56:14,512 --> 00:56:17,139
Come on, Kate.
加油，凯特

789
00:56:17,307 --> 00:56:19,308
Let's take on the little son of a bitch.
让我们把这个狗娘养的，

790
00:56:19,476 --> 00:56:23,271
Let's kick his ass
all the way back to Wall Street.
把他们踢回到华尔街去

791
00:56:51,590 --> 00:56:54,175
It's a quiet place.
这是一个安静的地方

792
00:56:54,343 --> 00:56:58,013
I thought it would be a good idea
if we calmed down a bit.
我认为我们冷静一点是个好主意

793
00:56:58,222 --> 00:57:00,724
Do you like Japanese?
你喜欢日本吗？

794
00:57:00,891 --> 00:57:02,851
I'd like to have Sony.
我喜欢索尼产品

795
00:57:03,060 --> 00:57:05,061
Could you bring me a knife and fork?
你能给我拿刀和叉吗？

796
00:57:11,068 --> 00:57:13,069
So, what do you say?
所以，你觉得怎么样？

797
00:57:14,905 --> 00:57:17,824
A proxy fight? I'd have to be nuts.
代理战？我会疯的

798
00:57:18,742 --> 00:57:21,536
I could sit on my ass and wait
for the injunction to lift...
我会坐下来等禁令解除……

799
00:57:21,703 --> 00:57:23,037
...buy all the shares I need.
……买入所有我需要的股票。

800
00:57:23,205 --> 00:57:25,790
Anybody else,
I wouldn't even come to lunch.
我不想其它任何人来分一杯羹

801
00:57:27,375 --> 00:57:29,168
You look very nice today.
你今天看起来非常漂亮

802
00:57:30,086 --> 00:57:33,714
But if you win, Lawrence,
it speeds up the process.
所以如果你雇员了，劳伦斯，就加快了进程。

803
00:57:33,882 --> 00:57:38,219
You get what you want in three months
instead of a year, maybe two.
在这三个月内你会得到你想要的，而不是一年，也许二年。

804
00:57:38,970 --> 00:57:40,888
I love it when you call me Lawrence.
我喜欢你叫我劳伦斯

805
00:57:41,055 --> 00:57:42,347
Say it again.
再说一次

806
00:57:46,102 --> 00:57:49,146
There's a lot can stand
in your way, Lawrence.
你会遇上很多阻碍，劳伦斯

807
00:57:49,314 --> 00:57:51,232
Anti-takeover legislation's
in the works.
现在有反收购立法

808
00:57:51,399 --> 00:57:53,651
Drexel's gone under. Milken's in jail.
德崇垮了，米尔肯现在在监狱里。

809
00:57:53,818 --> 00:57:55,444
Trump's waiting tables.
川普正在被传唤

810
00:57:55,611 --> 00:57:56,945
Don't threaten me.
不要恐吓我

811
00:57:57,155 --> 00:58:01,575
And just maybe you're over-leveraged,
and you can't afford to wait.
也许你正在负债中，所以你不能等

812
00:58:02,451 --> 00:58:05,287
- Thank you. You got any bread?
- No bread.
-谢谢，你有任何面包类的东西吗？
-没有面包

813
00:58:05,454 --> 00:58:07,038
No bread.
没面包

814
00:58:07,790 --> 00:58:09,458
They got no bread.
他们不吃面包

815
00:58:09,667 --> 00:58:12,419
They wanna run the world,
they got no bread.
他们想统治世界，可他们不吃面包。

816
00:58:15,297 --> 00:58:19,509
In three weeks, you present your own slate.
If you win, you buy everybody out at 2O.
三个星期内，你提交你的预案，
如果你赢了，我们以每股20元卖给你。

817
00:58:19,677 --> 00:58:22,137
If you lose, you sell us back
your shares at 1 5.
如果你输了，我们以15元每股买回你的份额

818
00:58:22,346 --> 00:58:25,515
Worst-case scenario,
you still make a couple million.
最坏的情况，你仍然挣好几个百万

819
00:58:27,017 --> 00:58:29,185
Amazing people, the Japanese.
日本人是令人惊讶的民族

820
00:58:29,812 --> 00:58:31,146
We blow the hell out of them.
我们用核弹炸了他们

821
00:58:31,313 --> 00:58:34,357
They go back to school, learn English
and start to run the world.
他们回到学校，开始学英语并准备统治世界

822
00:58:34,524 --> 00:58:35,816
What do we do?
我们做了什么?

823
00:58:35,984 --> 00:58:38,611
We get bigheaded,
start living the good life.
我们自大的过着美好的生活。

824
00:58:38,820 --> 00:58:40,154
Forget about schools.
没有学校

825
00:58:40,322 --> 00:58:42,240
People can't read. People can't write.
人不能读，不能写

826
00:58:42,449 --> 00:58:44,826
Country's full of dropouts.
全国满是辍学者

827
00:58:44,951 --> 00:58:46,827
Education.
教育

828
00:58:46,995 --> 00:58:50,081
Who needs education as long
as you can blow up the world?
要炸掉整个世界的人才需要教育？

829
00:58:50,290 --> 00:58:54,085
Meanwhile, I got everybody
in my office learning Japanese.
这意味着，我要办公室的每个人都学习日语

830
00:58:56,629 --> 00:58:58,589
I've never seen such a beautiful lawyer.
我还没有见过这么漂亮的律师

831
00:59:00,717 --> 00:59:02,385
Come on, Lawrence.
来吧，劳伦斯

832
00:59:02,552 --> 00:59:04,428
This is your game.
这是你的游戏

833
00:59:06,264 --> 00:59:08,265
Winner takes all.
赢家通吃

834
00:59:11,310 --> 00:59:13,395
Rumor has it, you got balls.
有传言说，你得到球了

835
00:59:15,064 --> 00:59:17,649
I've been trying to show you for weeks.
这几个星期我一直想告诉你

836
00:59:18,776 --> 00:59:20,944
Well, here's your opportunity.
嗯，现在你有机会了。

837
00:59:22,947 --> 00:59:24,865
All right.
好的

838
00:59:25,074 --> 00:59:27,910
I can always use
a good proxy bloodbath.
我随时可以使用一个很好的代理屠杀。

839
00:59:28,077 --> 00:59:30,329
After all, I wanna give you
a fighting chance.
毕竟，我想给你一个战斗的机会

840
00:59:30,538 --> 00:59:32,665
I love you.
我爱你

841
00:59:34,834 --> 00:59:36,502
Of course you do.
你当然

842
00:59:38,671 --> 00:59:40,798
Because we're the same.
因为我们是同一类人

843
00:59:43,008 --> 00:59:44,884
We are not the same, Lawrence.
我们是不一样的，劳伦斯

844
00:59:45,052 --> 00:59:46,803
Now, don't go spreading that around.
所以现在，不要这样去别跟人讲

845
00:59:46,970 --> 00:59:48,846
You know what makes us the same...
你知道我们在哪一样……

846
00:59:49,014 --> 00:59:51,099
...what sets us apart?
……哪里不一样？

847
00:59:52,100 --> 00:59:55,520
We care more about the game
than we do the players.
我们都关心这场游戏甚于做选手

848
00:59:57,105 --> 00:59:59,232
Oh, is that so?
哦，是这样吗？

849
01:00:00,067 --> 01:00:01,943
Yeah...
是的……

850
01:00:02,110 --> 01:00:04,237
...that's so.
……就是那样

851
01:00:16,791 --> 01:00:19,168
I'm gonna nail you, Lawrence...
我要抓住你……，劳伦斯

852
01:00:19,878 --> 01:00:22,046
...and everybody
on Wall Street's gonna know...
……华尔街上的每个人都将知道……

853
01:00:22,255 --> 01:00:24,548
...some broad did you in.
……一些你不为人知的一面

854
01:00:28,845 --> 01:00:32,223
You're so perfect for me.
你太抬举我了

855
01:00:33,850 --> 01:00:36,727
- I have to go.
- Don't go.
-我必须走了
-不要走

856
01:00:38,271 --> 01:00:40,314
Lunch is on me, baby-poo.
午餐很合我意，宝贝

857
01:00:43,484 --> 01:00:44,860
Where you going?
你要去哪？

858
01:00:45,236 --> 01:00:47,196
I have to go back to the office.
我要回办公室

859
01:00:48,322 --> 01:00:50,907
Don't go back to the office.
Come and work for me.
不要回去办公室，来为我工作。

860
01:01:02,378 --> 01:01:05,172
Lady said to say, "We have no doughnuts."
那女士要我告诉你，“我们没有甜甜圈。”

861
01:01:35,493 --> 01:01:37,786
Here's your coffee, boss.
老板，这是你的咖啡

862
01:01:44,502 --> 01:01:47,004
You make me feel like a dirty crook.
你使我感觉像一个肮脏的骗子

863
01:01:47,171 --> 01:01:50,465
Sneaking off to Jersey is not my style.
偷偷去新泽西不是我的风格

864
01:01:53,177 --> 01:01:55,512
Can we speak frankly?
我可以坦率的说吗？

865
01:01:56,305 --> 01:01:57,639
No. Lie to me.
不，骗我吧

866
01:01:57,807 --> 01:02:00,351
Tell me how thrilled you are
to know me.
告诉我你有多兴奋认识我

867
01:02:00,518 --> 01:02:05,230
I always speak frankly. I hate people
who say, "Can we speak frankly?"
我总是说的很坦率，我恨别人说，“我可以坦率地说吗？”

868
01:02:05,398 --> 01:02:08,734
It means they're bullshitting me
the rest of the time.
这意味着在剩下的时间里他们在蒙我

869
01:02:10,694 --> 01:02:12,695
I'm listening.
我在听

870
01:02:15,866 --> 01:02:17,367
Now...
现在……

871
01:02:18,744 --> 01:02:24,291
...as you know, I had 8O, OOO shares
of New England stock when we first met.
……你知道，当我们第一次见面的时候我持有8万股新英格兰电线电缆的股份

872
01:02:25,584 --> 01:02:29,212
What am I getting, a history lesson here?
Get to the point.
我得到什么，历史课？讲重点

873
01:02:29,421 --> 01:02:35,385
Since becoming aware
of your investments...
自从意识到你在投资……

874
01:02:35,552 --> 01:02:40,223
...I bought an additional 4O, OOO shares.
I now have 1 OO, OOO shares.
……我又增持了4万股份。我现在有10万个份额了

875
01:02:40,432 --> 01:02:42,934
Congratulations.
恭喜

876
01:02:43,977 --> 01:02:46,270
I'm prepared...
我准备……

877
01:02:48,356 --> 01:02:50,900
...to sell you the right...
……卖给你权利……

878
01:02:51,484 --> 01:02:54,820
...to vote those shares
at the annual meeting.
……在年度会议上投票

879
01:02:56,239 --> 01:02:58,366
How much?
多少钱

880
01:03:01,202 --> 01:03:03,996
- A million.
- Too much.
-一百万
-太多了

881
01:03:04,163 --> 01:03:07,624
You need a million shares
more than you already own.
你需要更多的一百万股比你已经拥有的

882
01:03:08,584 --> 01:03:12,587
Now, I can get you 1 O percent
of the way there in one transaction.
现在，只要一个交易你能得到10%的份额

883
01:03:12,755 --> 01:03:16,216
Better still, it's votes
they're counting on for themselves.
更好的是，他们依靠自己的股份投票

884
01:03:16,342 --> 01:03:19,678
They lose 1 O percent,
you gain 1 O percent.
他们失去10%，你就获得10%

885
01:03:19,845 --> 01:03:21,555
If you make a difference...
如果你到时变卦……

886
01:03:21,722 --> 01:03:24,975
...if I win by less than 1 OO, OOO votes,
you got your million.
……或如果我没用到这10万的选票就赢了，你就挣了一百万了。

887
01:03:25,101 --> 01:03:27,978
Otherwise, I don't need them,
I won't vote them.
另外，我不需要它们，我不会投票

888
01:03:28,145 --> 01:03:29,980
I'm not selling you an option.
我不是卖给你一个选择

889
01:03:30,147 --> 01:03:32,232
I'm selling you the right
to vote the shares.
我是卖给你这些股票的投票权利

890
01:03:32,399 --> 01:03:35,235
If they make a difference,
you got a million.
如果他们不干了，你就挣了一百万美元

891
01:03:35,402 --> 01:03:38,905
If they don't, half a million.
如果他们不干了，半百万

892
01:03:44,703 --> 01:03:46,955
I've prepared the papers.
我准备好的文件

893
01:03:47,873 --> 01:03:51,543
Left the numbers blank.
You can have your lawyers look at them.
除了数据是空白的，你可以让你的律师看看

894
01:03:53,962 --> 01:03:57,131
Everybody looks out for their own
self-interest, don't they?
每个人都顾自己的利益，不是吗？


895
01:03:57,924 --> 01:04:01,510
"What's in it for me?"
Isn't that what it's finally all about?
“我有什么好处？”这是不是所有事情的最终方式？

896
01:04:19,571 --> 01:04:20,822
Yes. Very good. Very good.
可以，完成的不错，非常不错

897
01:04:20,989 --> 01:04:22,782
- When do we run in the Times?
- Tomorrow.
-什么时候登在泰晤士报上
-明天

898
01:04:22,949 --> 01:04:25,659
- Times, Barron's, Forbes...
- Boston Herald.
-泰晤士，巴伦，福布斯……
-波士顿先驱报

899
01:04:25,827 --> 01:04:28,704
- Next week, major cities in New England.
- Great.
-下周，在新英格兰的主要城市
-太好了

900
01:04:28,913 --> 01:04:32,333
Take this copy and slide it
all over to the right.
把所有这些备份都标上所属

901
01:04:32,458 --> 01:04:34,751
And up in the corner here,
put that picture of me.
在这上面的角落里放我的照片

902
01:04:34,961 --> 01:04:37,088
- You know?
- You look good in that shot.
-你知道吗？
-这样你会看上去很不错

903
01:04:37,630 --> 01:04:39,840
Oh, God. Look at him.
听，上帝，看看他

904
01:04:40,007 --> 01:04:42,592
He's trying to look like Desmond Tutu.
他想让自己看起来像德斯蒙德

905
01:04:49,767 --> 01:04:51,518
All right, Richard, get our ad agency.
好了，李察，找我们的广告代理

906
01:04:51,685 --> 01:04:53,853
- Call Barbaro. Call Pinelli.
- Barbaro,  Pinelli.
-打电话给巴巴罗，派尼。
-芒派，尼里

907
01:04:53,979 --> 01:04:57,107
- Yeah. Where's that phone call from Tokyo?
- I'm on it,
-是的，这是从东京打来的电话吗？
-我来着手处理

908
01:05:16,585 --> 01:05:19,004
Taxi. Taxi!
出租车

909
01:05:30,807 --> 01:05:32,225
Thanks, Ron.
谢谢，荣恩

910
01:05:36,646 --> 01:05:38,856
Mr. Garfield's office.
加菲尔德先生的办公室

911
01:05:39,023 --> 01:05:41,608
I expect him back at 5:3O.
Thanks, Connie.
我希望他能在5:30回来
谢谢，康妮

912
01:05:41,776 --> 01:05:44,403
I'll ask him to phone you.
Bye-bye.
我会叫他给你打电话
再见

913
01:05:53,454 --> 01:05:55,789
Look, I found it. I found it.
看，我找到它了，我找到它了

914
01:05:57,708 --> 01:06:00,794
Mrs. Sullivan. She insisted
on waiting for you.
沙利文夫人，她坚持在等你

915
01:06:01,629 --> 01:06:04,798
I would appreciate a few moments
of your time.
我可以占用你的一点时间吗

916
01:06:05,383 --> 01:06:08,093
Certainly.
Hey, come on in the office.
当然
嘿，来我的办公室吧

917
01:06:09,095 --> 01:06:11,180
- Hold my calls.
- Will do.
-帮我接电话
-我会的

918
01:06:12,473 --> 01:06:14,808
Come on in. Have a seat right there.
进来吧，在这坐

919
01:06:14,975 --> 01:06:17,894
Did your daughter send you?
Because she's full of clever moves.
是你女儿让你来的？因为她充满了聪明的行动

920
01:06:18,020 --> 01:06:21,440
No, she didn't. She would be
very upset with me if she knew.
不，没有，如果她知道驰会非常生气

921
01:06:22,107 --> 01:06:24,943
I like Kate. She's quite the tomato.
我喜欢凯特，她很可人

922
01:06:25,110 --> 01:06:26,861
She must have taken after you, huh?
她一定是学你的，嗯？


923
01:06:27,029 --> 01:06:28,405
You're very kind.
你很亲切

924
01:06:28,572 --> 01:06:32,283
I would hope this meeting
will be held in confidence.
我希望这次的会议是私下的

925
01:06:32,451 --> 01:06:35,245
Everybody's looking
for confidence these days.
这些天，每个人都想私下的谈

926
01:06:35,412 --> 01:06:37,413
You want a cup of coffee?
你要一杯咖啡吗？

927
01:06:38,123 --> 01:06:41,292
- Cup of tea? Glass of water?
- You needn't be sociable, Mr. Garfield.
-一杯茶？或一杯水？
-你不必是交际的，加菲尔德先生

928
01:06:41,460 --> 01:06:43,003
- Harriet, cup of coffee.
- Yes.
-哈丽特，一杯咖啡
-是的

929
01:06:43,170 --> 01:06:44,588
You mind if I smoke?
你介意我吸烟吗？

930
01:06:46,798 --> 01:06:48,966
I'd like to tell you why I'm here.
我想告诉你我为什么在这里

931
01:06:50,093 --> 01:06:52,345
Good. Shoot.
好的，说吧

932
01:06:57,851 --> 01:07:01,187
I'm here to plead for our company.
我在这里为我的公司恳求

933
01:07:01,563 --> 01:07:05,817
I want to talk to you
about hopes and dreams...
我想和你谈谈关于希望和梦想……

934
01:07:06,109 --> 01:07:08,069
...traditions.
……传统的。

935
01:07:08,861 --> 01:07:11,446
Would you care for a doughnut,
Mrs. Sullivan?
你要一个甜甜圈吗？沙利文太太

936
01:07:11,614 --> 01:07:14,408
We've worked so hard
to build this company.
为建设这个公司我们工作很努力

937
01:07:14,575 --> 01:07:16,952
We're debt-free...
我不没有债务……

938
01:07:17,119 --> 01:07:20,121
...and we don't deserve to lose it.
……我们不应该失去它

939
01:07:20,581 --> 01:07:23,542
I want you to call off your fight with us.
我想让我们的斗争结束

940
01:07:26,504 --> 01:07:29,882
There's a trust fund in my name
with a million dollars in it.
在我的名义下有一个信托基金，里面有一百万美元

941
01:07:30,049 --> 01:07:32,759
I'll turn it over to you if you go away.
如果你离开，我就把它交给你

942
01:07:33,302 --> 01:07:35,012
You don't wanna do that.
你不想那么做的

943
01:07:35,137 --> 01:07:39,849
We'll buy back your shares at cost,
plus you'll have a million dollars profit.
我们会用成本价买回你手中的股票，加入你将获得一百万美元的利润

944
01:07:41,852 --> 01:07:43,061
Interesting.
有意思

945
01:07:43,479 --> 01:07:46,648
I know a million dollars
isn't much money to you...
我知道一百万美元对你来说不是很多……

946
01:07:46,773 --> 01:07:49,317
...but if I had more, I'd give it to you.
……但如果我有更多，我都会给你

947
01:07:49,735 --> 01:07:51,319
Who are you doing it for?
你这样做是为了谁？

948
01:07:52,195 --> 01:07:54,113
Money's not that important to me.
钱对我来说并不是很重要

949
01:07:54,656 --> 01:07:58,326
- Well, it is to me.
- Then accept my offer.
-咽，我看重它
-那接受我的提议

950
01:07:58,618 --> 01:08:02,663
You'll have more money
than most people make in a lifetime.
你会有更多的钱比大多数人的一辈子

951
01:08:02,831 --> 01:08:04,582
A million dollars.
一百万美元

952
01:08:05,292 --> 01:08:07,168
It's not enough.
这不够

953
01:08:08,378 --> 01:08:09,962
Go home, Mrs. Sullivan.
回去吧，沙利文夫人

954
01:08:11,297 --> 01:08:14,174
I'd hoped to appeal
to your sense of decency.
我希望唤醒你的良知

955
01:08:15,218 --> 01:08:17,011
I'm sorry.
很抱歉

956
01:08:17,137 --> 01:08:20,974
I don't take money from widows
or orphans. I make them money.
我不从寡妇和狐儿那挣钱，我为他们挣钱

957
01:08:21,516 --> 01:08:25,311
Before or after you put them out
of business?
让他们从生意中出局之前还是之后？

958
01:08:45,164 --> 01:08:47,124
What a woman.
什么样的女人

959
01:08:48,084 --> 01:08:51,462
Harriet, why do I always bring out
the best in people?
哈丽特，为什么我总是拿出最出的一面亲民

960
01:09:40,843 --> 01:09:42,386
Hello?
您好？

961
01:09:43,471 --> 01:09:45,181
Hello?
您好？

962
01:09:45,598 --> 01:09:47,891
Oh, please,
哦，拜托！

963
01:09:51,813 --> 01:09:53,314
Arthur!
亚瑟！

964
01:09:53,481 --> 01:09:56,650
Get the car. Arthur.
去取车，亚瑟

965
01:10:02,406 --> 01:10:05,742
I'm sorry, sir. There's no answer
in Miss Sullivan's apartment.
先生，抱歉，沙利文小姐的公寓没有回复

966
01:10:05,910 --> 01:10:08,746
Well, try it again.
Maybe you dialed it wrong.
嗯，再试一次，可能你拨错号了

967
01:10:14,460 --> 01:10:16,170
No!
不

968
01:10:18,589 --> 01:10:21,550
Excuse me, Bart.
What are you doing here?
请原谅，巴特
你在这干什么？

969
01:10:21,717 --> 01:10:24,511
- Who's Bart?
- I'm on my way out. You should've called.
-巴特是谁?
-我正要出去，你应事先来电话的

970
01:10:24,678 --> 01:10:26,846
- I need to talk to you.
- I don't have time...
-我需要和你谈谈
-我没时间了……

971
01:10:27,014 --> 01:10:29,724
I have something important to tell you.
I need to talk now.
我有些重要的事要告诉你
我需要现在就说

972
01:10:29,850 --> 01:10:33,395
- You look beautiful. Who's this guy?
- Excuse me, Lawrence. Call me tomorrow.
-你看上去真漂亮，那个家伙是谁?
-抱歉，劳伦斯，明天给我电话

973
01:10:33,562 --> 01:10:36,439
I can't talk tomorrow. It won't keep.
我不能等到明天谈

974
01:10:38,191 --> 01:10:40,192
I want you to marry me.
我要你嫁给我

975
01:10:40,360 --> 01:10:41,819
Let me put it another way.
换句庆说

976
01:10:41,987 --> 01:10:44,155
I wanna marry you.
我想取你

977
01:10:45,657 --> 01:10:47,075
You thinking it over?
你考虑过吗？

978
01:10:47,951 --> 01:10:50,453
- What are you talking about?
- What do you mean?
-你在说什么？
-你什么意思？

979
01:10:50,620 --> 01:10:53,956
I want you to be my wife.
We belong together.
我想你成为我的妻子
我们属于一起

980
01:10:54,666 --> 01:10:57,460
- I'm going to the opera. I gotta go.
- No, no, Kate.
-我正要去歌剧院，我要走了
-不，不，凯特

981
01:10:59,504 --> 01:11:02,965
You're the last thought I have
when I fall asleep at night...
你是我入睡时最后想念的人……

982
01:11:03,091 --> 01:11:06,010
...and the first when I wake up
in the morning.
……和早上醒来最先想念的人

983
01:11:06,469 --> 01:11:09,305
I wanna be with you forever and ever.
我想和你永远在一起

984
01:11:10,139 --> 01:11:12,599
I wanna have babies with you.
我想和生孩子

985
01:11:13,518 --> 01:11:16,145
- Babies?
- Yeah.
-孩子？
-是的

986
01:11:16,729 --> 01:11:21,191
You see, I gotta do this now,
because after I win...
你看，我得现在这么做，因为在我赢了后……

987
01:11:21,359 --> 01:11:24,987
...maybe you won't wanna speak to me.
- You can't win. I'm gonna win.
……也许你不会想跟我说话了。
-你不能赢，我要赢。

988
01:11:25,196 --> 01:11:28,532
I know how important it is to you,
but you're not gonna win.
我知道它对你有多重要，但你不会赢

989
01:11:28,949 --> 01:11:30,617
This is what's killing me.
这个对来我说很要命

990
01:11:30,826 --> 01:11:34,329
I want you. I need you. I love you.
I just don't wanna lose you.
我想你，我需要你，我爱你
我只是不想失去你

991
01:11:34,496 --> 01:11:37,332
- Katherine.
- Keep your pants on, will you, Bart?
-凯瑟琳
-镇定，你会吧，巴特？

992
01:11:37,499 --> 01:11:40,877
- I've gotta go.
- All right, the opera. La Traviata.
-我得走了
-好，歌剧，茶花女

993
01:11:41,045 --> 01:11:44,506
You don't wanna miss the first act.
It sets up the whole thing.
你不想错过第一幕
你建立了整个事情


994
01:11:58,228 --> 01:12:00,229
It's a wonderful production.
这是一个好作品

995
01:12:04,734 --> 01:12:06,610
Have a good time.
玩的高兴

996
01:12:53,365 --> 01:12:55,575
I'm gonna lose her, Arthur.
亚瑟，我会失去她的

997
01:13:28,858 --> 01:13:30,776
Oh, I've been looking for you.
哦，我一直在找你

998
01:13:31,861 --> 01:13:33,737
Anytime you're ready.
只要你准备好

999
01:13:35,573 --> 01:13:37,199
You okay?
你还好吗？

1000
01:13:38,201 --> 01:13:39,619
Yeah.
是的

1001
01:13:39,786 --> 01:13:42,496
Just going over in my mind
what I wanna say.
我正在构思我要说什么

1002
01:13:42,664 --> 01:13:44,832
They're putting speakers outside.
他们正把音箱放在外面

1003
01:13:45,458 --> 01:13:49,169
I think every shareholder
within driving distance is coming.
我认为每一个在开车距离内的股东都会来


1004
01:13:49,337 --> 01:13:52,757
I feel as if we're Harry and Bess
on election night.
我觉得我们就像选举之夜时的哈里和贝丝

1005
01:13:52,924 --> 01:13:56,886
Harry Truman was a better man than me.
He slept on election night.
哈里・杜鲁门比我强
他能在大选之夜睡着

1006
01:13:57,094 --> 01:13:59,888
I haven't slept in days.
我几天没睡好了

1007
01:14:00,973 --> 01:14:04,351
Talk to me. Tell me.
跟我谈谈，告诉我

1008
01:14:06,771 --> 01:14:08,689
I'm scared.
我害怕

1009
01:14:10,274 --> 01:14:12,109
I'm scared that...
我害怕……

1010
01:14:14,737 --> 01:14:17,364
...time has passed us by.
……时间从我们身边流逝

1011
01:14:20,075 --> 01:14:23,495
I'm scared I don't know
this new environment.
我害怕我不认识这个新环境

1012
01:14:23,954 --> 01:14:27,916
I'm scared that what I do know
doesn't count for anything anymore.
我害怕我知道这不算什么

1013
01:14:28,083 --> 01:14:30,168
Things have changed.
事情已经改变了

1014
01:14:31,295 --> 01:14:35,549
Whatever happened
to people serving each other?
无论和这些共患难的人之间发生了什么？

1015
01:14:38,844 --> 01:14:42,430
I don't want this man to win.
我不想这个人赢

1016
01:14:44,391 --> 01:14:46,184
I'm not scared.
我不害怕

1017
01:14:46,351 --> 01:14:48,436
I'm just proud.
我为你骄傲

1018
01:14:50,021 --> 01:14:53,315
I'm proud of the business we've built.
我为我们已经建立的业务骄傲

1019
01:14:54,400 --> 01:14:56,485
I'm so proud of you.
我为你骄傲

1020
01:14:57,445 --> 01:15:00,614
And if what we are
counts for nothing anymore...
如果我们不是什么了……

1021
01:15:00,782 --> 01:15:03,284
...then that's their failing, not ours.
……那是他们的失败，不是我们。

1022
01:15:06,412 --> 01:15:08,330
It'll be all right.
它会没事的

1023
01:15:09,415 --> 01:15:11,500
Just go out and tell the truth.
只要走出去，并告诉真相

1024
01:15:14,712 --> 01:15:17,214
Go out and give them hell, Harry.
出去给他们一击，哈利。

1025
01:15:25,931 --> 01:15:28,058
Good luck to us all today, Bill.
今天祝我们所有人好运，比尔。

1026
01:15:28,225 --> 01:15:31,436
I feel we're gonna be just fine.
我觉得我们会好的

1027
01:15:36,608 --> 01:15:40,403
Looks like they've come from everywhere.
New York, Boston.
看来他们来自各处。纽约，波士顿。

1028
01:15:40,529 --> 01:15:44,574
- There's Ozzie.
- Happening all over, isn't it?
-那是奥兹
-发生了，不是吗？

1029
01:15:44,908 --> 01:15:47,243
Everybody looking out for themselves.
每个人都在为他们自己

1030
01:15:51,331 --> 01:15:54,333
So did you get
your golden parachute, Bill?
所以你得到了你的金色降落伞了，比尔？

1031
01:15:54,501 --> 01:15:56,586
Did he finally promise to take care of you?
他最终答应照顾你了？

1032
01:15:57,838 --> 01:16:00,590
Lord of the manor, house on the hill.
在山上房子的庄园主

1033
01:16:01,424 --> 01:16:06,470
Said he didn't want to talk about a funeral
while there was no corpse.
说他不想谈没有尸体的葬礼

1034
01:16:14,312 --> 01:16:17,440
Well, time to go.
好了，是走的时候了

1035
01:16:19,067 --> 01:16:20,610
Bill.
比尔

1036
01:16:22,987 --> 01:16:24,363
How you gonna vote?
你要如何投票？

1037
01:16:44,925 --> 01:16:48,636
Oh, boy. They're out in droves, Arthur.
They got the kids here.
哦，伙记。他们正成群结队的，亚瑟。
他们把孩子带到这儿来了

1038
01:16:48,762 --> 01:16:50,972
Why do they always bring the kids,
Arthur?
为什么他们总是把孩子带过来,亚瑟？

1039
01:16:54,685 --> 01:16:58,480
That's right. Hooray, hooray.
Down with Garfield.
对哦，万岁，万岁，打倒加菲尔德

1040
01:17:10,325 --> 01:17:11,951
Okay, TV crews.
好了，电视工作人员

1041
01:17:12,119 --> 01:17:14,037
Financial News Network, here we come.
财经新闻网，我来了

1042
01:17:20,210 --> 01:17:21,961
Mr. Garfield!
加菲尔德！

1043
01:17:22,128 --> 01:17:24,505
What are your plans
for New England Wire and Cable?
你怎么计划新英格兰电线电缆公司？

1044
01:17:24,673 --> 01:17:25,965
Make the stockholders richer.
让股东挣变得更富裕

1045
01:17:26,132 --> 01:17:30,177
Will you liquidate New England Wire and
Cable? And if so, what about the workers?
你会解散新英格兰电线电缆公司吗？如果会，那工人怎么办？

1046
01:17:30,387 --> 01:17:34,474
My obligation is to the stockholders.
The board of directors make that decision.
我对股东负责。
董事会会做出决定

1047
01:17:34,641 --> 01:17:36,392
Oh, come on!
噢，得了吧！

1048
01:17:39,020 --> 01:17:41,105
What about the workers?
工人怎么办？

1049
01:17:41,272 --> 01:17:44,108
Are they gonna lose their jobs?
Come on, answer the question.
他们会失去他们的工作吗？来吧，回答这个问题

1050
01:17:44,275 --> 01:17:46,235
Come on, Mr. Garfield!
来吧，加菲尔德！

1051
01:17:47,320 --> 01:17:50,197
How do you feel about the outcome
of today's proxy vote?
你觉得今天的代理投票会有怎样的结果？

1052
01:17:50,323 --> 01:17:53,826
I feel confident that the shareholders
will vote their consciences.
我深信，股东会凭良知投票的

1053
01:17:53,993 --> 01:17:56,203
I have every confidence
in this company's future.
我对公司的未来很有信心

1054
01:18:37,077 --> 01:18:39,329
Could I have your attention, please?
请大家安静一下？

1055
01:18:39,496 --> 01:18:41,080
Welcome to...
欢迎光临……

1056
01:18:41,248 --> 01:18:45,377
...New England Wire and Cable's
annual stockholders' meeting.
……新英格兰电线电缆年度股东大会

1057
01:18:45,543 --> 01:18:49,797
I'm William J. Coles, your president,
and I'm sure...
我是威廉・科尔斯，你们的总经理，我肯定……

1058
01:18:51,132 --> 01:18:55,094
I'm sure that everyone here realizes
the most important item on the agenda...
我确信在这里的每个人实现最重要的一项议程……

1059
01:18:55,553 --> 01:18:58,097
...is the election
of the board of directors.
……是选举公司的董事

1060
01:18:58,264 --> 01:19:03,519
Now, there are staff members
passing out the ballots.
现在，工作人员在发选票

1061
01:19:03,978 --> 01:19:07,523
Right now, I am very proud
to introduce to you...
现在，我很自豪地向你们介绍……

1062
01:19:07,732 --> 01:19:12,987
...a man who could accurately
be characterized as a legend...
准备的说，一个有传奇色彩的人……

1063
01:19:13,196 --> 01:19:15,239
...in the wire and cable industry.
……在电线电缆行业

1064
01:19:15,656 --> 01:19:19,534
The chairman of the board
of New England Wire and Cable...
新英格兰电线电缆公司的董事会主席……

1065
01:19:19,702 --> 01:19:21,286
...Mr. Andrew Jorgenson.
……安得烈・乔根森先生

1066
01:19:44,017 --> 01:19:45,393
Give them hell, Andy!
安迪，让他们见鬼去吧

1067
01:19:47,187 --> 01:19:49,981
It's good to see so many...
很高兴看到这么多……

1068
01:19:50,148 --> 01:19:53,568
...familiar faces, so many old friends.
……熟悉的面孔，这么多老朋友

1069
01:19:54,027 --> 01:19:56,946
Some of you I haven't seen in years.
你们有些人我很久没见过了

1070
01:19:57,114 --> 01:19:59,115
Thank you for coming.
谢谢你的光临

1071
01:19:59,241 --> 01:20:04,079
Bill Coles, our able president,
in the annual report, has told you...
比尔科尔斯，我们的总经理，在年度报告中，已经告诉你……

1072
01:20:04,204 --> 01:20:08,041
...of our year, of what we accomplished,
of the need for further improvements...
……这一年我们所完成的，及需要做进一步改进的……

1073
01:20:08,208 --> 01:20:13,212
...our business goals for next year
and the years beyond.
……我们企业明年的目标和多年以后的

1074
01:20:18,593 --> 01:20:21,554
I'd like to talk to you
about something else.
我想和你们谈谈其它事情

1075
01:20:23,306 --> 01:20:25,808
I want to share with you
some of my thoughts...
我想和你们分享我的一些想法……

1076
01:20:26,017 --> 01:20:31,647
...concerning the vote that you're going
to make in the company that you own.
……关于你们将要投票的你们自己的公司

1077
01:20:31,939 --> 01:20:37,444
This proud company, which has survived
the death of its founder,,,
这个令人骄傲的公司，依然幸存，历经创始人去世、

1078
01:20:37,611 --> 01:20:42,907
,,, numerous recessions,
one major depression and two world wars,,,
……众多次衰退，一次大萧条和两次世界大战……

1079
01:20:43,534 --> 01:20:49,247
,,, is in imminent danger
of self-destructing,
……现在却正面临自我毁灭的威胁

1080
01:20:49,957 --> 01:20:54,377
On this day, in the town of its birth,
就在今天，就在这座它诞生的小镇

1081
01:20:58,590 --> 01:21:02,593
There is the instrument
of our destruction.
这就是要解散我们公司的家伙

1082
01:21:03,720 --> 01:21:08,558
I want you to look at him in all of his glory.
"Larry the Liquidator."
我想你们看看他，及他所有的荣耀
“清算人拉里”


1083
01:21:08,892 --> 01:21:14,856
The entrepreneur of post-industrial America
playing God...
后工业时代美国的企业家扮演着上帝……

1084
01:21:15,023 --> 01:21:17,817
...with other people's money.
……用别人的钱

1085
01:21:19,694 --> 01:21:25,407
The robber barons of old at least
left something tangible in their wake.
即使是旧时代的强盗大亨在他们身后也会留下一些可触摸的东西

1086
01:21:25,784 --> 01:21:29,120
A coal mine, a railroad, banks.
一个煤矿，铁路，银行

1087
01:21:29,996 --> 01:21:32,248
This man leaves nothing.
这个人什么也没留下

1088
01:21:32,415 --> 01:21:35,626
He creates nothing.
He builds nothing.
他什么也没创造
他什么也不建造

1089
01:21:35,793 --> 01:21:38,253
He runs nothing.
他什么也不经营

1090
01:21:39,797 --> 01:21:45,093
And in his wake lies nothing
but a blizzard of paper to cover the pain.
在他后，什么也不会留下，除了带来灾难的成堆文件

1091
01:21:45,303 --> 01:21:51,308
Oh, if he said, "I know how to run
your business better than you"...
哦，如果他说，“我知道如何把生意做的比你更好……”

1092
01:21:51,475 --> 01:21:54,060
...that would be something
worth talking about...
……那还值得谈谈……

1093
01:21:54,228 --> 01:21:56,188
...but he's not saying that.
……但他并没有那样说

1094
01:21:56,355 --> 01:22:02,194
He's saying, "I'm gonna kill you
because at this particular moment in time...
他说“我会杀了你，因为在这个特定的时刻……

1095
01:22:02,319 --> 01:22:05,029
...you're worth more dead than alive."
……你死了比活着更值钱。”

1096
01:22:05,197 --> 01:22:06,698
Well...
好吧……

1097
01:22:07,157 --> 01:22:10,785
...maybe that's true, but it is also true...
……可能那是事实，但是这也是真的

1098
01:22:10,953 --> 01:22:14,873
...that one day this industry will turn.
……就是会有一天这个行业会走好。

1099
01:22:15,082 --> 01:22:20,086
One day when the yen is weaker,
the dollar is stronger...
当日元疲软，美元走强的那一天……

1100
01:22:20,295 --> 01:22:25,716
...or when we finally begin
to rebuild our roads, our bridges...
……或当我们开始重建我们的道路，桥梁……

1101
01:22:25,926 --> 01:22:30,513
...the infrastructure of our country,
demand will skyrocket.
……我国的基础设施，需求会激增

1102
01:22:30,639 --> 01:22:35,185
And when those things happen,
we will still be here...
当这些发生时，我们仍然会在这里……

1103
01:22:35,393 --> 01:22:40,981
...stronger because of our ordeal,
stronger because we have survived.
……更强壮因为经历为考验，
更强壮因为我们存活了下来。

1104
01:22:41,149 --> 01:22:46,946
And the price of our stock
will make his offer pale by comparison.
我们股票到时价格走高，会让他现在的收购价相形失色

1105
01:22:47,447 --> 01:22:53,035
God save us if we vote to take
his paltry few dollars and run.
上帝会拯救我们，如果我们投票决定注入一些小资金让其运行

1106
01:22:54,120 --> 01:22:59,166
God save this country
if that is truly the wave of the future.
上帝会拯救这个国家如果这确实是未来的浪潮

1107
01:22:59,459 --> 01:23:02,670
We will then have become a nation
that makes nothing but hamburgers...
我们将会成一个专做汉堡的的民族……

1108
01:23:02,795 --> 01:23:07,799
...creates nothing but lawyers
and sells nothing but tax shelters.
……一无所造除了律师，一无所卖除了避税避税服务


1109
01:23:07,967 --> 01:23:12,638
And if we are at that point in this country
where we kill something...
如果我们在这个点，在这个国家杀死什么……

1110
01:23:12,805 --> 01:23:18,310
...because at the moment
it's worth more dead than alive...
就因为此刻死比活值得更多……

1111
01:23:18,436 --> 01:23:19,979
...well...
……好吧

1112
01:23:20,354 --> 01:23:23,732
...take a look around. Look at your
neighbor. Look at your neighbor.
……看看周围，看看你的邻居

1113
01:23:23,899 --> 01:23:26,943
You won't kill him, will you? No.
你不会杀死他，对吧？你不会

1114
01:23:27,111 --> 01:23:29,988
It's called murder, and it's illegal.
这被称作是谋杀，并且这也是非法的

1115
01:23:30,114 --> 01:23:34,159
Well, this, too, is murder,
on a mass scale.
嗯，这，也是谋杀，一个大规模的

1116
01:23:34,326 --> 01:23:40,748
Only on Wall Street,
they call it maximizing shareholder value...
只有在华尔街，
他们称它为股东价值最大化……

1117
01:23:40,999 --> 01:23:43,084
...and they call it legal.
……他们称它是合法的。
1118
01:23:43,252 --> 01:23:47,672
And they substitute dollar bills
where a conscience should be.
他们用美元钞票取代了良心的位置

1119
01:23:48,382 --> 01:23:50,050
Damn it!
该死！

1120
01:23:50,258 --> 01:23:54,512
A business is worth more
than the price of its stock.
业务运营比其股价更具价值

1121
01:23:55,388 --> 01:23:59,266
It's the place where we earn our living,
where we meet our friends...
这是我们谋生和会见朋友的地方……

1122
01:23:59,434 --> 01:24:01,769
...dream our dreams.
……梦想我们的梦想

1123
01:24:01,937 --> 01:24:07,400
It is, in every sense, the very fabric
that binds our society together.
它是，从每个意义上，是我们社会紧密连接在一起的构造

1124
01:24:07,984 --> 01:24:10,945
So let us now, at this meeting...
所以让我们现在，在这次会议上……

1125
01:24:11,112 --> 01:24:14,865
...say to every Garfield in the land...
……对这片土地上的每一个加菲尔德说……

1126
01:24:15,033 --> 01:24:20,121
...here, we build things,
we don't destroy them.
……在这里，我们建立事物，我们不毁灭他们

1127
01:24:20,288 --> 01:24:24,625
Here, we care about more
than the price of our stock.
在这里，比起股票价格我们在乎更多的东西


1128
01:24:25,084 --> 01:24:26,752
Here...
在这里……
1129
01:24:28,045 --> 01:24:30,213
...we care about people.
……我们在乎人

1130
01:24:54,863 --> 01:24:56,239
Thank you.
谢谢

1131
01:24:57,991 --> 01:25:02,495
And now I'd like to introduce
Mr. Lawrence Garfield.
现在我想介绍劳伦斯加菲尔德先生

1132
01:25:02,663 --> 01:25:05,665
Mr. Gar...
Excuse... Please.
加……   对不起，等一下

1133
01:25:05,832 --> 01:25:08,834
Let's show a little courtesy,
ladies and gentlemen.
让我们表现出一点礼貌，女士们，先生们。

1134
01:25:09,711 --> 01:25:13,589
Mr. Garfield is the president
and the chairman of the board...
加菲尔德是总经理和委员会主席……

1135
01:25:13,965 --> 01:25:16,258
...of Garfield Investments.
……加菲尔投资公司

1136
01:25:16,426 --> 01:25:18,302
Mr. Garfield.
加菲尔德先生

1137
01:25:39,907 --> 01:25:41,575
Amen.
阿门

1138
01:25:42,952 --> 01:25:44,703
And amen.
阿门

1139
01:25:45,663 --> 01:25:47,331
And amen.
阿门

1140
01:25:47,540 --> 01:25:51,210
You have to forgive me.
I'm not familiar with the local custom.
你必须原谅我，我不熟悉当地的风俗

1141
01:25:51,377 --> 01:25:56,173
Where I come from, you always say amen
after you hear a prayer.
我来的那个地方，当你听完祷告后你总是说阿门

1142
01:25:57,008 --> 01:25:59,552
Because that's what you just heard.
那是因为你刚听到的

1143
01:25:59,719 --> 01:26:01,470
A prayer.
一个祈祷者

1144
01:26:03,264 --> 01:26:05,432
Where I come from...
我从那里来……

1145
01:26:06,183 --> 01:26:11,563
...that particular prayer
is called the prayer for the dead.
……那个特别的祈祷被称为“为死祈祷”

1146
01:26:13,482 --> 01:26:17,861
You just heard the prayer for the dead,
my fellow stockholders...
你刚听到了为死亡的祈祷，各位股东……

1147
01:26:18,028 --> 01:26:20,530
...and you didn't say amen.
……你没有说阿门

1148
01:26:21,865 --> 01:26:24,158
This company is dead.
这个公司死了

1149
01:26:24,868 --> 01:26:27,704
I didn't kill it. Don't blame me.
我没有杀它，不要责怪我

1150
01:26:27,871 --> 01:26:30,581
It was dead when I got here.
当我到这里的时候，它已经死了

1151
01:26:33,710 --> 01:26:36,462
It's too late for prayers.
作祈祷太晚了

1152
01:26:39,341 --> 01:26:43,178
For even if the prayers were answered
and a miracle occurred...
甚至如果祈祷有回应，那奇迹就发生了……

1153
01:26:43,345 --> 01:26:45,805
...and the yen did this
and the dollar did that...
……日元这样，美元那样……

1154
01:26:45,972 --> 01:26:50,101
...and the infrastructure did the other thing,
we would still be dead.
……和基础设施的其他东西，象刚才所说那样
我们仍然会死。

1155
01:26:50,643 --> 01:26:52,227
You know why?
你知道为什么吗？

1156
01:26:53,730 --> 01:26:55,815
Fiber optics.
纤维光学

1157
01:26:56,190 --> 01:26:58,775
New technologies.
新技术

1158
01:27:00,361 --> 01:27:02,863
